<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Just a quickie. The Troll race, and Troll Blood corruption should both bestow a light vulnerability. If Bill, Tom and Bert could be killed by light, then I personally think that the players should have the same disability. The other possibility is that Trolls could be “turned to stone” (i.e. paralysed) when hit by a light attack. The only disadvantage to this is that daylight is close to instadeath without light resistance, so pure non-paralysing damage would probably be better for game balance.  <p>
2cworth and counting…  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: I think the player character trolls are supposed to be of the improved Olog breed, so it makes sense for them to withstand the sun. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: From The Encyclopaedia of Arda: <em>Olog-hai - A race of trolls bred by Sauron in the later years of the Third Age, seen among the trees of southern Mirkwood, and the mountain borders of Mordor. They were superior to other trolls in almost every way: stronger and more powerful, but also showing greater intelligence and skill. Many of their abilities they owed to being under the direct will of their master, Sauron, and while under his control they could exist in direct sunlight, unlike others of their kind. </em> Fair enough! The interesting bit here is the "Direct will of their master" bit. Maybe only Morgoth-worshippers should be allowed to stand sunlight! &lt;jk&gt; More seriously though, an acquired affect from the Troll Blood corruption would (to me) make more sense than intrinsic aggravate... 
</p>
